Heads up — we're installing MSBuild v17 (Visual Studio 2022 Build Tools) on the self-hosted runner today/tomorrow.

If your workflow uses microsoft/setup-msbuild@v2, it will automatically pick up the new version after the install. If you want to keep using the current MSBuild (VS 2017), you'll need to add the vs-version input to your workflow:

- name: Add msbuild to PATH
  uses: microsoft/setup-msbuild@v2
  with:
    vs-version: '[15.0,16.0)'
